cation><abstract id="abstract"><p id="p-0001" num="0000">A detection device (<b>7</b><i>a</i>) for determining the orientation of a first and a second wheel (<b>2</b>) of a vehicle (<b>3</b>), the wheels being arranged on a first side of the vehicle (<b>3</b>) with respect to a longitudinal axis thereof (A). The device is set laterally with respect to the vehicle (<b>3</b>) on the first side, between the first and second wheels, and has a first (<b>8</b>) and a second image&#x2014;acquisition elements (<b>8&#x2032;</b>) located on a base support (<b>16</b>) having a respective viewing area (V) for acquiring images of a first and a second target (<b>5</b>) coupled to the first and second wheels, respectively. A displacement unit (<b>10</b>) is operatively coupled to the first (<b>8</b>) and second (<b>8&#x2032;</b>) image-acquisition elements for rotating them simultaneously through one and the same angle of rotation so as to adapt their viewing area to the position of the first and second targets (<b>5</b>). The detection device (<b>7</b><i>a</i>) further comprises additional alignment sensors (<b>27</b><i>a, </i><b>27</b><i>b, </i><b>28</b><i>a, </i><b>28</b><i>b</i>) also located on the base support (<b>16</b>) for measuring calibration parameters of the base support (<b>16</b>).</p></abstract></us-patent-application>